Exercise 05 — Return-to-libc (NX Bypass)
==========================================

The stack is no longer executable.
Injecting shellcode (exercise 02) is now blocked by the CPU.

Instead, you will reuse code already loaded in memory.
The C standard library (libc) contains system() and the
string "/bin/sh" — all you need for a shell.

Your goal: call system("/bin/sh") by chaining existing addresses.
Once you have a shell, run: echo [SUCCESS]
